  "prompt": "How much sleep does the US President get every night?",
  "response": "The amount of sleep the U.S. President gets each night can vary based on individual habits and the demands of the job. Historically, many U.S. Presidents have reported getting less sleep than the average person due to their busy schedules and responsibilities. For instance, President Donald Trump was known to sleep around 4-5 hours a night, while President Barack Obama reportedly averaged about 6 hours per night.\n\nHowever, exact details about the current President's sleep patterns might not be publicly disclosed, and it can also vary over their term in office based on personal health, workload, and other factors. Generally, it is recognized that the role of President can be extremely demanding and may impact typical sleep routines.",
